Replication Broken between Kafka 0.8.2.1 and 0.9 - NetworkClient.java uses wrong protocol version - During a rolling upgrade from 0.8.2.1 to 0.9.0.0, replication between 0.9.0.0 and 0.8.2.1 fails due to
org.apache.kafka.clients.networkClient:handleCompletedReceives always using the latest version of the API Key available instead of the one specified by inter.broker.protocol.version.

